          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Medal of Honor Surviving Spouses Recognition Act of 2016</strong></p> <p>This bill requires the payment of a Medal of Honor special pension to the surviving spouse of a deceased Medal of Honor recipient if that person was married to the recipient for: (1) at least one year; or (2) any period of time if a child was born of the marriage, or was born to them before the marriage.</p> <p>The special pension for a living Medal of Honor recipient is increased to $1,299.61 per month. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-02-04T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
